     - But from `2ⁿ ≡ -1 mod p`, raising to the `(p - 1)/2` power gives `2ⁿ⁽ᵖ⁻¹⁾/² ≡ (-1)⁽ᵖ⁻¹⁾/² mod p`. Since `2ⁿ⁽ᵖ⁻¹⁾/² ≡ 1 mod p` (by Fermat's Little Theorem if `(p - 1)/2` is a multiple of the order of `2` modulo `p`), but `(-1)⁽ᵖ⁻¹⁾/² ≡ 1 mod p` if `p ≡ 1 mod 4` or `-1` if `p ≡ 3 mod 4`, we get contradictions if `p ≡ 3 mod 4`.
